snippet.textDisplay:
Just to educate y’all there’s 3 different kinds of births

Natural Delivery
Vaginal Delivery
C-Section Delivery

Natural -No epidural, no medication delivering baby vaginally.

Vaginal-Epidural, other medication if necessary, delivering baby vaginally.

C-Section- Spinal Block, delivering baby through serious abdominal surgery.

snippet.textDisplay: Brought me to tears... lol i found out I was prego and weeks later you announced you were prego and turned out your due date was 3 days after mine.. I could relate to you throughout all these months.. went to my last check up at 39 weeks 5 days and they told me there water sack was empty and baby did not want to move and she was probably dying already and to head to the hospital immediately for an emergency c section and girl I felt my whole world drop 😭 I was crying and praying and speeding to the hospital rubbing my belly asking bbyg to please move and please hold on 😭 got to the hospital and  ran to check in was trying so hard to hold the tears in and keep my voice from cracking while speaking to the nurses I could barely take in what they were telling me I was lost in my thoughts & feelings and they put me on the monitor and said she still has a heartbeat but I would get induced later at night and see if I dilated fast enough to not have to do a c section since my original plan was to push .. got induced at around 11-12am and was holding my precious baby by 6am Thursday morning dec 19th 🥺❤️ still haven’t been able to soak in all the emotions I felt and am currently feeling... Congratulations les ❤️ he is so precious 🥺🥰 wish you and Alex and baby g the best and may his health stay good 😇
